<body>
Reports cases when you try to drop columns from indexed tables. This inspection is available in Microsoft SQL Server and Sybase ASE.
<p>Example (Microsoft SQL Server):</p>
<pre><code>CREATE TABLE test_index
(
col  INT NOT NULL,
col2 INT NOT NULL,
col3 INT NOT NULL UNIQUE,
col4 VARCHAR(200)
);

CREATE UNIQUE INDEX aaaa ON test_index (col, col2);

ALTER TABLE test_index
DROP COLUMN col;</code></pre>
<p>You cannot delete the <code>col</code> column because it is in the indexed table. To delete the column, you need to delete the
  <code>aaaa</code> index first (for example, DROP INDEX aaaa).</p>
